===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|まち|yomi=k|alt=街,坊}}
From {{inh|ja|ojp|-}}, with the original meaning of “[[plot]] of [[land]]”<ref name="JDB">{{R:JDB|page=680}}</ref>. Vovin argues it is likely borrowed from an ancestor to {{cog|okm|맡|t=[[field]]}} <ref name="KJ">{{R:jpx:Vovin 2010|page=192}}</ref>, but all Japanese etymological theories base the etymology on the meaning of “[[town]]; [[section]] of a [[castle]] town”, typically using {{ja-r|道|ち}}, {{ja-r|道|みち|[[road]]}}.<ref name="KDJ2O"/>

